name: Target

name: Cartel Coffee

name: Lowe's of Orchard Park

comment: Men,  Women,  and Unisex/Handicapped restrooms

name: Target
directions: It's in a hallway on the front wall of the store. After heading in the store, head toward the center, and there will be a hallway with restrooms. There is a single-use Family restroom to the right in front of the stalled gendered restrooms.

name: Woodland Hills Mall
directions: If you enter through Sears and exit into the mall (first floor), walk past a few of stores on the wall to your right, and there will be a hall to the right that leads you to the bathrooms. A single-use Family restroom is located toward the end of the hall, on the left, right in front of the entrances to the stalled gendered restrooms.

name: Walmart
directions: Right in the middle of the back of the store, behind the electronics section - the photo lab. When you go back into the photo lab area you will immediately notice two stalled gendered restrooms on the left, and then a door to the backroom on the back wall. Right next to the backroom door is a single-use Family restroom.
comment: You should not have any issue using this one - the employees do all of the time.

name: Valley West Mall
directions: 2nd floor, by JC Penny and Kim's Tailor. There are two family restrooms that admit only one person/family at a time.

name: 10501 Holly Springs Dr, Houston, TX 77042, USA
Genova
directions: 5th floor, room 14
comment: I give you so much fun

name: NEA Community Learning Center
directions: Left wall upon entrance to school. Another is located if you go right, down, and right again from the area right beyond the door of the school.
comment: It is single stall and sometimes crowded.

name: Etscorn Honors Center
directions: Down the hall on the right, 2 matching gender neutral restrooms.
comment: The people at the desk might ask you what you're doing, but "using the restroom" should be a good answer.

name: Kentucky Science Center
directions: Third floor TimeZone gallery, near Gravball exhibit.
comment: Must be a paid visitor to the museum.

name: Wonder Book & Video
directions: Follow the bright handmade signs hanging from the ceiling :)

name: Maya Cinema
directions: The bathroom is located down the hall where the films are being played
comment: you must pay to see a film before you are allowed in the building

name: Sweetgreen
directions: Behing the seating area, two unisex bathrooms labeled "WC"
comment: Do not have to be a paying customer but they're food is so good one would recommend!

name: Spruce Confections
directions: In the back of the courtyard to the east of the cafe
comment: Needs a key, which is on a whisk on a hook by the door. Employees don't care about who takes the key and there's no policy around the bathroom.

name: Swain Resort (Children's Learning Center)
directions: The blue door at the cafeteria area.  It's  unmarked.
comment: Only avaliable when the CLC is open.  Check hours before you go.

name: The Lamb
directions: Straight down the corridor when you enter, turn right and it's  immediately on the left.
comment: You don't have to enter the actual bar, so you don't need to buy a drink. It's a disabled loo.

name: Charlotte Premium Outlets
directions: In between Lane Bryant and New York & Company Outlet.
comment: It's in the Management Building, there's a sign that says Restrooms. It's a single stalled Family restroom in between the gendered restrooms. Very nice!

name: 563 5 Cities Dr, Grover Beach, CA 93433, USA
directions: Am/pm gas station

name: SF Bio
comment: At a movie theater, so just walking in and using the toilet might look a little strange.

name: Wonder Book & Video
directions: Look for a big colorful handmade sign hanging from the ceiling - that'll point you the right direction.

name: Wonder Book & Video
directions: Look for a big colorful handmade sign hanging from the ceiling - that'll point you the right direction.

name: Wizarding World of Harry Potter, Diagon Alley
directions: Head straight to Gringots, the. Take a left. Go down to the end of the alley and on the right are bathrooms. Two of them are single-stall "family" restrooms

name: Wonder Books
directions: Against the back wall - follow the colorful sign :)

name: Wonder Books
directions: Against the back wall - follow the colorful sign :)

name: Bower Ashton Campus

name: Starbucks
street: Junction One Outlet Centre, Ballymena Road
directions: Past the cash register, towards the back of the store on your right.
comment: They may question you if you aren't a paying customer but there's no code on the door, so you could go without getting anything.

name: Old Bag Of Nails Pub
directions: Turn right when you head in the doors and follow all of the way back.
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Walmart (Victor)
directions: Towards the service desk and hang a left.

name: Veihmeyer Hall, Davis, CA 95616, USA
directions: 1st floor under the stairs at the end of the hallway near the door. Not wheelchair accessible

name: Hill County Rest Stop
directions: In the inside area, next to the vending machines
comment: Just walk in and go into it - marked family restroom. Huge with a bench and one toilet and sink. Also free WiFi and the vending machines take debit/credit cards :D

name: Costa
directions: Go in and up the stairs, around the corner and straight forward
comment: No one should bother you even if you don't buy anything

name: Mia's Fabric Cafe
comment: Bathroom is in the back work room, just ask whoever greets you where it is.

name: Pizza Colore
directions: Back of the restaurant to the left.

name: Valero
directions: Towrads back, past sodas
comment: Single restroom,  friendly staff, decently clean(for a gas station)

name: Costa Coffee
directions: At the back of the shop, just around a corner

name: Alpha brewing company
directions: Alpha is in the back of the building on Lucas ave
comment: The staff is friendly. You are supposed to be a paying customer but that is rarely enforced.

name: Mt. Tom's homemade ice cream and candy store
directions: Free door on the right, ask staff very friendly.
comment: Very friendly staff, used to people entering for the bathroom and leaving.

name: Hobby Lobby
directions: In the front of the store, turn and go straight left after you walk in. It's a single stalled family restroom.
comment: You should browse the store a little bit, at least the aisles at the front on the way to the restroom. They have some neat things!

name: The bake house
directions: Walk in through the front door. Toilet is straight ahead on back wall
comment: Paying customers

name: Jalan Sultan Mansor, Taman Tasik Taiping, 34000 Taiping, Perak, Malaysia
Cherry Creek High School
directions: Across from IC cafe, two gender-neutral bathrooms.
comment: Sometimes one is locked by faculty. Another is always unlocked for student use.

name: Rowan Cabarrus Community College
directions: On the second floor of the 1000 building (the main building in the middle and the floor you walk in on.) Walk down the short and only hallway and you will find it, it's closer to the side the 3000 building is next to.
comment: You probably should be a student or teacher or valid visitor but you just have to walk in the building and go to it, it's a single stall labeled 'Restroom'.

name: AMC Theaters
directions: There are two Unisex restrooms, one at each end of the theater, past the gendered restrooms and outside of some of the movie theater rooms.
comment: You have to be there to see a movie as you need a movie ticket to get to where it is.

name: Cold Lake Public Library
directions: Behind the circulation desk, to the left in a little hallway.

name: Savor Flavor Asia
directions: The restrooms are located in the back left of the restaurant, down a small hallway.
comment: The restrooms are two single gendered stalls.  They are labeled as accessible.

name: Stockton University
directions: Directly across the art gallery by the PAC and the other two gendered restrooms.
comment: This is the worst bathroom on campus, I'm not sure which of the two locks work, the tile is falling off from the walls, there is obvious signs of water damage, and the sink is too small and might be to high for someone that uses a wheelchair but it is at least an option.

name: Stockton University
directions: F wing has three floors, the basement, middle, and top, it is the middle floor. Go behind the big staircase and down that hallway.
comment: One toilet in a stall that locks, one urnal. The door of the restroom also locks if needed.

name: Domino's
comment: Don't have to be a customer, its a one toilet bathroom

name: Sunrise Cafe
directions: From the front entrance, it's on the left, in the hallway past the kitchen.
comment: Open 7am-3pm daily. They would probably prefer if you were a customer, but no signs require it. http://www.yelp.com/biz/sunrise-caf%C3%A9-lakewood-3

name: GLBT Community Center of Colorado
directions: Ask for key at front dest for upstairs bathroom. Youth only bathroom in basement.
comment: Check at front desk first.

name: Sparky's Roadside Barbecue
directions: Back of the restroom, no boy girl signs on either. Furthest one has a urinal
comment: No need to pay. Just ask for the restroom.

name: Access Nova Scotia
directions: To the right just as you come in the doors

name: Guildford Town Centre
directions: 3 family washrooms that are gender neutral. First is by food court, other is by upper center court, and last is downstairs from Entrance 6.

name: Deans Diner
directions: At the back of the restaurant
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: San Francisco State University Humanities Building
directions: 2 single stall gender neutral restrooms on the first floor nearest the entrance that is adjacent to the fine arts and creative arts buildings.

name: Savery Hall
directions: On the mezzanine level, to the right of the elevators

name: San Francisco State University J Paul Leonard Library
directions: Single stall gender neutral/family restroom located on the basement level in the same hallway as the gendered restrooms. Accessible by elevator or if you enter on the basement level on the side of the library nearest the creative arts building.

name: New Moon Cafe Downtown Aiken
comment: I know all the staff of all New Moon's locations are trans friendly and these restrooms are always safe.  The owner is a huge ally.  Been a few years since I was at this location, don't remember where in the cafe, but it is a safe place to answer the call of nature.

name: New Moon Cafe Downtown Augusta
directions: Hallway to the left of the counter and kitchen.  2 gender neutral bathrooms.
comment: The preference is customers only, but if you are respectful, the staff knows that sometimes you just gotta have a safe, clean place to go and won't hassle you, just come in and go.

name: Loso Hall, EOU
directions: Loso Hall, go to the hall left of the gallery, walk all the way to the back. Two gender neutral bathrooms should be to your right
comment: One has a single stall and a urinal, the other has two single stalls. Bathrooms are obviously marked as neutral

name: Navy Federal Credit Union
directions: Once through front doors go down the right side of the lobby all the way to the back. Two bathrooms are there on the left.

name: Chorlton Green Brasserie
directions: Walk almost to the back of the restaurant, toilet is on the left hand side. Single unisex toilet
comment: Paying customers only

name: Rosie's coffee house
directions: Go in through main door of the cafe, walk straight ahead past the counter and turn left. Unisex single stall bathroom
comment: Ideally for paying customers

name: Simon building (ground floor)
directions: Walk through the cafe in to the main building, unisex bathroom on right hand side.
comment: University of Manchester building, you don't have to be a paying customer and you don't need ID or anything

name: Little Federal Store, Westown
directions: Its the only bathroom and its a unisex single stall. Pretty easy to find its just through the doors and next to the food cabinet
comment: They are very friendly and have good food! I don't think they would mind if you had to use the bathroom without buying anything, but you can always just buy a milkshake or something if you feel as though you're being rude.

name: Starbucks
comment: There's no bathroom code or key and the restrooms are right by the door so it's easy to duck in and out.

name: Diablo Valley College - Book Center
directions: There's a single unisex bathroom to the left of the Peet's Coffee counter in the book center. Hardly anyone uses it.

name: Fuller Park
directions: Across from the playground between gendered stalls there are two "family" closed single stall rooms.

name: Fuller Park
directions: Across from the playground between gendered stalls there are two "family" closed single stall rooms.

name: Burns Recreation Center, Loyola Marymount University
directions: Walk past the locker rooms, there is a family restroom! Single stall and even has a shower. Stall is handicap accessible, not sure about shower
comment: You may not be able to use it if you're not an LMU student/faculty as you have to swipe your ID to get into the gym.

name: Otis College of Art and Design
directions: Building labeled Ahmanson, lower level.
comment: It's a college so just act like you belong.

name: Opie's Deli
directions: Upstairs, they aren't labeled at all so you may have to ask.
comment: Should let you in without a problem, if not the food is great and cheap anyway.

name: Edmonson Hall (Collins Living-Learning Center), Bloomington, IN 47408, USA
directions: to the left of the main doors or to the right of the side door on the dining hall level
comment: open to anyone

name: Honors College
street: 210 Oak View Hall  2200 N. Squirrel Road
directions: Coming in the west doors by the big parking lot, just inside

name: Allied Media & Cinema Detroit
directions: Down small hall
comment: Unisex and gendered bathrooms. Safe space

name: Italian Village Pizza
directions: By the back
comment: You should buy something, the pizzas pretty cheap anyway

name: Crazy Mocha
directions: It's to the left of the counters.
comment: You should probably buy something

name: Starbucks
comment: Since they're single stalls it's never a problem, and no customers ever give second looks. But if they do, the baristas will usually defend you!
